org.rsna.ctp.stdstages.anonymizer.xml

Class XMLAnonymizer

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.rsna.ctp.stdstages.anonymizer.xml.XMLAnonymizer

  • public class XMLAnonymizer
extends java.lang.Object
    The MIRC XML anonymizer. This anonymizer provides de-identification and re-identification of XML objects for clinical trials. Each element is scriptable. The script language is documented on the MIRC wiki. See the MIRC wiki for more more information.

    • Method Detail

      • anonymize

        public static AnonymizerStatus anonymize(java.io.File inFile,
                         java.io.File outFile,
                         java.io.File cmdFile)
        Anonymizes the input file, writing the result to the output file. The fields to anonymize are scripted in the properties file.
        Parameters:
        inFile - the file to anonymize.
        outFile - the output file. It may be same as inFile you if want to anonymize in place.
        cmdFile - the file containing the anonymization commands.
        Returns:
        AnonymizerStatus.OK if successful; AnonymizerStatus.QUARANTINE otherwise, in which case the input file is not modified.

      • anonymize

        public static AnonymizerStatus anonymize(org.w3c.dom.Document xmlDocument,
                         java.io.File cmdFile)
        Anonymize a DOM Document.
        Parameters:
        xmlDocument - the object to anonymize
        cmdFile - the file containing the anonymization commands.
        Returns:
        AnonymizerStatus.OK if successful; AnonymizerStatus.QUARANTINE otherwise. IMPORTANT: if the anonymization fails, the DOM Document may still have been at least partially modified.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - if the anonymization fails;
